---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Getting Started" activeNav="getting-started" description="Install reasoningtool and start using it.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Getting started</h1>
  </div>

  <section>
    <h2>Installation</h2>

    <div class="card-grid card-grid--2">
      <div class="card">
        <h3>Option 1: Run from the repo</h3>
        <pre><code>git clone https://github.com/benjam3n/reasoningtool.git
cd reasoningtool/claude-code-plugin
claude</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <h3>Option 2: Copy into your project</h3>
        <pre><code>cp -r path/to/reasoningtool/claude-code-plugin/skills your-project/
cp path/to/reasoningtool/claude-code-plugin/CLAUDE.md your-project/
cd your-project
claude</code></pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Examples</h2>
    <pre><code>/araw should I change careers

/se what are all the ways I could approach this product launch

/aex we need to hire 3 more engineers by Q2

/cmp React vs Svelte for this project

/rca our deploy pipeline keeps failing

/uaua 4x what's the best approach to learning math</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Which skill to use</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>You know&hellip;</th><th>Use</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Nothing</td><td><code>/uaua</code></td><td>Map possibilities, then test them</td></tr>
        <tr><td>You want to see what you're missing</td><td><code>/u</code></td><td>Explore the space</td></tr>
        <tr><td>You have a claim, unsure if right or wrong</td><td><code>/araw</code></td><td>Test both sides</td></tr>
        <tr><td>You believe something is right</td><td><code>/ar</code></td><td>Trace implications, foreclosures, costs</td></tr>
        <tr><td>You suspect something is wrong</td><td><code>/aw</code></td><td>Find failure reasons, derive alternatives</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <pre><code>Do you know what your options are?
├── NO → Do you need thorough analysis?
│   ├── YES → /uaua
│   └── NO, just show me what exists → /u
└── YES → Do you have a specific claim to test?
    ├── YES → Do you lean one way?
    │   ├── I think it's RIGHT → /ar
    │   ├── I think it's WRONG → /aw
    │   └── I genuinely don't know → /araw
    └── NO → /u (map first, then /ar or /aw on what you find)</code></pre>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Other skills</h2>

    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Skill</th><th>What it does</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>/sbfow</code></td><td>Output was rejected &mdash; figure out why</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/fowwr</code></td><td>Something failed &mdash; trace back to root cause</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/wt</code></td><td>"I want to X" &mdash; trace what that commits you to</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/foht</code></td><td>Know the goal, not the method &mdash; find methods</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/qo</code></td><td>Find the question that opens a document</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/w</code></td><td>Criteria-based writing</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Depth scaling</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Depth</th><th>What you get</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td><code>/araw</code></td><td>3&ndash;4 levels</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/araw 2x</code></td><td>4&ndash;5 levels</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/araw 4x</code></td><td>5&ndash;6 levels, edge cases</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/araw 8x</code></td><td>6&ndash;8 levels</td></tr>
        <tr><td><code>/uaua 4x</code></td><td>Alternating search at 4x depth</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Python tools</h2>
    <pre><code>pip install openai pyyaml
export OPENAI_API_KEY="sk-your-key"
cd src/araw

python auto_expand_llm.py --db career.db --seed "Should I start a business?"
python visualize.py --db career.db --serve</code></pre>
    <p><a href="/tools">Full tool documentation &rarr;</a></p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Don't praise output mid-conversation</h2>
    <p>Praising output shifts it toward producing what you liked rather than what's true.</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Challenge it: "That's wrong because..." or "You're missing..."</li>
      <li>Redirect it: "Now test that with /aw" or "Run /ar on the opposite claim."</li>
      <li>Stay neutral. Just ask for the next step.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</Base>
